3. **Implement a robust error handling mechanism**: In the event of an array length mismatch, provide a clear and informative error message to the user, indicating the specific arrays that have mismatched lengths. This will enable users to identify and address the issue promptly.

Example code snippet:
````
function executeRoutes(
    uint32[] calldata routeIds,
    bytes[] calldata dataItems,
    bytes[] calldata eventDataItems
) external payable {
    uint256 routeIdslength = routeIds.length;
    uint256 dataItemsLength = dataItems.length;
    uint256 eventDataItemsLength = eventDataItems.length;

    if (routeIdslength!= dataItemsLength || routeIdslength!= eventDataItemsLength) {
        // Revert the transaction if array lengths do not match
        assembly {
            revert(0, 0)
        }
    }

    // Continue with the execution of the transaction if array lengths match
